content:
Run and Use the Results of an Autolaunched Flow on the Same Screen with the New Action Button Component (Beta)

Add an Action Button component to a flow screen to run and retrieve information from an active autolaunched flow without leaving the screen. The component renders a button that invokes the flow when clicked.

Create a screen that includes a Lookup component, add an Action Button component to launch a flow that retrieves Account, Case, and Opportunity records associated with the Contact record and populates other fields on the same screen.

This feature is a Beta Service. 

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: In Flow Builder, create and activate an autolaunched flow that retrieves data, then add a Screen element to the flow and include an Action Button on the screen. Configure the Action Button component to launch the autolaunched flow and add another element to ingest the retrieved data.

title: Run and Use Results of Autolaunched Flow
